cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the handover mechanism in wireless cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel method for handover optimization using reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of reinforcement learning in the proposed method makes it relevant to the artificial intelligence subcategory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a centralized RL agent to control the handovers between base-stations, which can be seen as a control system. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the performance of the proposed method using different propagation environments, which involves the study of information transmission and reception.
